Your testVariable is not static, it belongs to the instance of your activity, so it&#39;s normal that it is reset when you move to an other activity.
Passing variable to other activity using Intent is the appropriate way to share variables values between activities.

What you could do though, is build your app around a main application instance:

    import android.app.Application;
    
    public class YourOwnApplication extends Application {
        //...
        int testVariable;

        public int getTestVariable() {
            return testVariable;
        }

        public void setTestVariable(int testVariable) {
            this.testVariable = testVariable;
        }
    }


And declare your application class in your manifest:

    &lt;manifest xmlns:android=&quot;http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android&quot;
              package=&quot;com.you.yourapp&quot;&gt;
    
        &lt;application
            android:name=&quot;.YourOwnApplication&quot;

You can then access the variable and set its value from your activities:

    int testVar = ((YourOwnApplication )getApplicationContext()).getTestVariable()

